fields.name: imageWidth
fields.comment: The X size of the inventory window in pixels.

fields.name: imageHeight
fields.comment: The Y size of the inventory window in pixels.

fields.name: menu
fields.comment: A list of the players inventory slots

fields.name: leftPos
fields.comment: Starting X position for the Gui. Inconsistent use for Gui backgrounds.

fields.name: topPos
fields.comment: Starting Y position for the Gui. Inconsistent use for Gui backgrounds.

fields.name: isSplittingStack
fields.comment: Used when touchscreen is enabled.

fields.name: draggingItem
fields.comment: Used when touchscreen is enabled

fields.name: snapbackItem
fields.comment: Used when touchscreen is enabled

fields.name: sign
fields.comment: Reference to the sign object.

fields.name: frame
fields.comment: Counts the number of screen updates.

fields.name: line
fields.comment: The index of the line that is being edited.

fields.name: isModified
fields.comment: Whether the book's title or contents has been modified since being opened

fields.name: isSigning
fields.comment: Determines if the signing screen is open

fields.name: frameTick
fields.comment: Update ticks since the gui was opened

fields.name: lastClickTime
fields.comment: In milliseconds

fields.name: playTurnSound
fields.comment: Determines if a sound is played when the page is turned

fields.name: containerRows
fields.comment: Window height is calculated with these values" the more rows, the higher

fields.name: scrollOffs
fields.comment: Amount scrolled in Creative mode inventory (0 = top, 1 = bottom)

fields.name: scrolling
fields.comment: True if the scrollbar is being dragged

fields.name: horse
fields.comment: The EntityHorse whose inventory is currently being accessed.

fields.name: xMouse
fields.comment: The mouse x-position recorded during the last rendered frame.

fields.name: yMouse
fields.comment: The mouse y-position recorded during the last rendered frame.

fields.name: xMouse
fields.comment: The old x position of the mouse pointer

fields.name: yMouse
fields.comment: The old y position of the mouse pointer

fields.name: shopItem
fields.comment: The integer value corresponding to the currently selected merchant recipe.

fields.name: scrolling
fields.comment: Is {@code true} if the player clicked on the scroll wheel in the GUI.
